---
layout: layouts/page.njk
title: "Get in touch about Project Budget"
subtitle: "Bug reports, feature requests, accessibility issues, documentation gaps, or just a question — pick a topic and send a note. Replies usually land within a few business days."
description: "Get in touch about Project Budget — bug reports, feature requests, documentation gaps, accessibility issues, or general questions."
permalink: /contact/
---
<div class="contact-page">
  <div class="contact-page__grid">
    <aside class="contact-page__bio">
      <img src="/assets/img/jonajinga.webp"
           alt="Jon Ajinga, the maintainer of Project Budget"
           class="contact-page__photo"
           width="160" height="160" loading="lazy" decoding="async">
      <h2 class="contact-page__bio-name">Jon Ajinga</h2>
      <p class="contact-page__bio-role">Maintainer · Project Budget</p>
      <p class="contact-page__bio-body">
        I read every message personally. Project Budget is open source and developed in public — bug reports, accessibility issues, and feature ideas all shape the roadmap directly.
      </p>
      <ul class="contact-page__bio-links">
        <li>
          <strong>Email:</strong>
          <a href="mailto:{{ site.email }}">{{ site.email }}</a>
          <span class="contact-page__bio-hint">Direct line for anything not suited to the form below.</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Docs:</strong>
          <a href="/docs/">Read the documentation</a>
          <span class="contact-page__bio-hint">Most "how do I…" questions already have an answer here.</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Glossary:</strong>
          <a href="/glossary/">Browse plain-English definitions</a>
          <span class="contact-page__bio-hint">If a budgeting term is tripping you up, it's probably defined here.</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </aside>

    <section class="contact-page__form-card">
      <h2 class="contact-page__form-heading">Send a message</h2>
      <p class="contact-page__form-intro">
        Pick a topic from the dropdown so the message routes correctly. All fields marked <span class="contact-page__req">*</span> are required.
      </p>

      <form id="contactForm"
            data-web3forms
            data-redirect="/thank-you/"
            action="https://api.web3forms.com/submit"
            method="POST"
            class="contact-form">
        <input type="hidden" name="access_key" value="b6c3454b-f07c-43f7-9070-0e0cb5286f55">
        <input type="hidden" name="subject" value="Project Budget — new contact form submission">
        <input type="hidden" name="from_name" value="Project Budget contact form">
        {# Honeypot — bots fill it; humans never see it. #}
        <input type="checkbox" name="botcheck" tabindex="-1" autocomplete="off" style="position:absolute;left:-9999px;width:1px;height:1px;opacity:0;">

        <div class="contact-form__row">
          <div class="contact-form__field">
            <label for="cf-name">Your name <span class="contact-page__req">*</span></label>
            <input type="text" id="cf-name" name="name" required autocomplete="name" placeholder="Jane Doe">
          </div>
          <div class="contact-form__field">
            <label for="cf-email">Email <span class="contact-page__req">*</span></label>
            <input type="email" id="cf-email" name="email" required autocomplete="email" placeholder="jane@example.com">
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="contact-form__field">
          <label for="cf-topic">What's this about? <span class="contact-page__req">*</span></label>
          <select id="cf-topic" name="topic" required>
            <option value="">Pick a topic so I can route your message…</option>
            <option value="Bug report">Bug report — something is broken or behaving unexpectedly</option>
            <option value="Feature request">Feature request — something you'd like added or improved</option>
            <option value="Accessibility">Accessibility issue — a barrier to using the app</option>
            <option value="Documentation">Documentation — a topic that's missing, wrong, or unclear</option>
            <option value="Data import">Data import — help with CSV / OFX / QIF / QFX files</option>
            <option value="Profiles & backups">Profiles &amp; backups — questions about local storage or exports</option>
            <option value="Reports">Reports — questions about a specific report or chart</option>
            <option value="Privacy / security">Privacy or security concern</option>
            <option value="Partnership">Partnership, integration, or collaboration</option>
            <option value="General question">General question — anything else</option>
          </select>
          <p class="contact-form__hint">Bug reports and accessibility issues get the fastest reply. For UI bugs, a screenshot helps a lot.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="contact-form__field">
          <label for="cf-severity">How urgent is this?</label>
          <select id="cf-severity" name="severity">
            <option value="Not urgent">Not urgent — whenever you get to it</option>
            <option value="Soon">Soon — affecting my budgeting workflow</option>
            <option value="Blocking">Blocking — I can't use the app until this is fixed</option>
          </select>
        </div>

        <div class="contact-form__field">
          <label for="cf-browser">Browser &amp; device (for bug reports)</label>
          <input type="text" id="cf-browser" name="browser" placeholder="e.g. Chrome 134 on Windows 11, or Safari on iPhone 15">
        </div>

        <div class="contact-form__field">
          <label for="cf-message">Message <span class="contact-page__req">*</span></label>
          <textarea id="cf-message" name="message" rows="7" required
                    placeholder="For bugs: what you tried, what happened, what you expected. For features: the problem you're trying to solve, not just the solution you have in mind."></textarea>
        </div>

        <div class="contact-form__actions">
          <button class="btn btn--primary" type="submit">Send message</button>
          <a class="btn btn--ghost" href="mailto:{{ site.email }}">Email directly instead</a>
        </div>

        <p class="contact-form__privacy">
          Your message goes to a single inbox I read personally. No tracking pixels, no marketing list — promise.
        </p>
      </form>
    </section>
  </div>
</div>
